  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nI am not certain of this, but I believe that test filters (when running `forge test --match-test XXX`) are applied AFTER forge tries to everything, even files that are not touched by the test XXX. \r\n\r\nThis is not ideal when testing only one behavior of a large codebase. \r\n\r\nYou might want to add `console.log` at specific points, and only test a very specific flow, but since all files impacted by the change are compiled before applying test filters, small changes may take a long time to run.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
